OL,3,C'He wasn't perfect but he didn't
OL,4,Cdeserve to die'
OL,6,FIn a statement, Mr Sharp's family
OL,7,Fsaid: "Paul wasn't perfect, but he
OL,8,Fwasn't a bad man and did not deserve
OL,9,Fto die in the way that he did.
OL,11,F"We ask that anyone with information
OL,12,Fto please come forward and speak to
OL,13,Fthe police. If this was your loved one
OL,14,Fyou would want people to do the same
OL,15,Fthing, cooperate with the police
OL,16,Finvestigation and do the right thing."
